"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The np.sinc function in numpy returns sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) at x=0 the sinc is 1, but at x=1 the sinc is sin(pi)/(pi) which is not zero but approximately 0.0 due to floating point precision. So the assertion sinc_result[1] == 0 will fail.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8\\n<assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n>assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], 0), \\\"Results not close to zero\\\"\"\n}"